@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="privacy-page-shell">
    <div class="privacy-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Privacy Charter</p>
        <h1 class="display-5">Starstay protects traveler and host signals across every orbit.</h1>
        <p class="section-copy">
            This privacy policy explains what Starstay collects, why it is collected, and how guest and host data
            is used while browsing listings, managing accounts, and booking starship stays.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-grid">
        <article class="privacy-card privacy-card-wide">
            <p class="starport-label">What We Collect</p>
            <h2>Account, listing, and booking data</h2>
            <p>
                When you register, Starstay stores account information such as your email address, display name,
                encrypted authentication credentials, and profile details needed to sign in and manage your stays.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you host, Starstay stores listing information you submit, including starship name, alien location,
                pricing, uploaded or linked images, stay summaries, and habitat compatibility details.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you book a voyage, Starstay stores reservation windows, total nebula credits, and optional arrival
                notes so hosts and travelers can coordinate the stay.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card">
            <p class="starport-label">Why We Use It</p>
            <h2>To run the marketplace</h2>
            <p>
                Starstay uses your data to authenticate accounts, publish listings, calculate bookings, prevent overlap
                conflicts, and show the correct information to the right host or traveler.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card">
            <p class="starport-label">Session Signals</p>
            <h2>Cookies and signed-in state</h2>
            <p>
                Starstay uses authentication and session cookies to keep you signed in, preserve your active session,
                and personalize parts of the interface such as traveler greetings and host controls.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card">
            <p class="starport-label">Marketplace Visibility</p>
            <h2>Public listing information</h2>
            <p>
                Starship listings are intended to be visible in the public marketplace. Travelers may see listing images,
                pricing, compatibility details, location names, and host-facing stay descriptions before signing in.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card">
            <p class="starport-label">Reservation Integrity</p>
            <h2>Booking protection and conflict checks</h2>
            <p>
                Booking details are used to block overlapping reservations, display upcoming voyages to signed-in users,
                and prevent hosts from deleting listings that already have active traveler commitments.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card privacy-card-wide">
            <p class="starport-label">Your Control</p>
            <h2>How to manage your data</h2>
            <p>
                You can update future listing content by editing or deleting host data that has not yet been tied to a live
                traveler booking. You can also choose what optional details to include in listings, such as habitat notes
                and compatibility features.
            </p>
            <p>
                Because Starstay is still an evolving prototype marketplace, this policy may be refined as messaging,
                payments, traveler history, and additional account tools are introduced.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="privacy-card privacy-card-wide">
            <p class="starport-label">Scope</p>
            <h2>Current Starstay environment</h2>
            <p>
                Starstay currently runs as an ASP.NET Core application with Identity, Entity Framework Core, SQL Server,
                and local static asset storage for listing imagery. This policy reflects the behavior of the app as it
                exists today in that environment.
            </p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
